<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12003h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12003h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12003h"> 3(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cascade de g&eacute;nitifs / jonglerie de substantifs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[they are trying to improve an ill-turned phrase in Raymond Radiguet&apos;s <cite>Diable au corps</cite>, &lsquo;Le tragique de cette folle sur un toit s&apos;augmentait de ce que la maison par&ucirc;t abandonn&eacute;e.&rsquo;]</font> Il serait fort classique de dire: &ldquo;Le tragique du spectacle s&apos;augmentait de l&apos;abandon de la demeure.&rdquo; C&apos;est encore lourd. Il y a des <mark>g&eacute;nitifs en cascade</mark>, ran&ccedil;on probable de cette <mark>jonglerie de substantifs</mark>. Que voulez-vous! On ne redresse pas les phrases mal constitu&eacute;es. On les envoie &agrave; la refonte. <br><font color="green">[It would all too old-fashioned to say: &ldquo;The tragedy of the spectacle was enhanced by the dereliction of the building.&rdquo; That is too heavy still. There is an avalanche of genitives as a result of an abundance of nouns. There is no way around it! You cannot repair clauses that are badly constructed. They have to be recast entirely.]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger &amp; Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="SOIR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SOIR"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 254</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
